race.comment: MIND YA BIZZ (11) resumes after coming out of a strong Maiden on debut when second over 1100m at Gosford in fast time. Two trials had merit and can finish over the top of these. MRS FLANDERS (12) total forgive from the wide gate when eighth over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Will race closer today from the inside gate and the 3kg claim keeps her in the contest. Value prospect. SEVEN DAYS (13) trained locally, and the blinkers come off first-up. Showed ability in two trials and looks set for a positive return. DON'T (1) is on debut today and comes into this with a couple of trials under his belt. Suspect he's had some issues being a 6YO at the races for the first time, though he must show something at home to persist for this long. Latest trial was solid and he creates some interest.
